The Confederation Africaine de Football (CAF) announces that the media accreditation process for the draw of the group phase of the Total CAF Confederation Cup 2018 opens from Tuesday, 10 April 2018 to Sunday, 15 April 2018. The draw will be held on Saturday, 21 April 2018 in Cairo, Egypt at 14h Cairo local time (12 GMT). Media interested in covering the draw of the group phase of the Total CAF Confederation Cup 2018 can apply for accreditation through the CAF Media Channel via www.cafonline.com. Approval to access the CAF Media Channel does not mean you have been granted accreditation. All applications are subject to confirmation. Confirmation will NOT be on a first-come, first-served basis. Successful applicants will be notified and provided with further information in due course. Furthermore, please be advised that international applicants are responsible for securing their own visas to Egypt. For more information on the draw of the group phase Total CAF Confederation Cup 2018, please visit our website www.cafonline.com. For general media enquiries, please contact; [email protected]